  "texts": [
    "The hierarchical learning architecture can be divided into three components, namely the word layer, sentence layer, and document layer.",
    "Word LayerIn order for the model to learn more text information from long documents, we divide the text into multiple sentences.",
    "Specifically, for a given long document, we represent it as a sequence of sentences S = {s 1,..., s n }, where s i = {w i,1,..., w i,m }, i = 1,..., n denotes the token sequence of the i th sentence.",
    "If necessary, each sentence will be padded and cut to maintain the same length.",
    "The Embedding layer encodes each word w i, j into a d-dimensional vector based on word embeddings."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}